  "instruction": "Write a Common Lisp macro `with-pid-file` that writes a process id stamp to a file at the given path, runs body, and deletes the file on exit. Use gensyms for the path and stream temporaries so callers cannot shadow them.",
  "reference_defmacro": "(defmacro with-pid-file (path &body body)\n  (let ((p (gensym)) (s (gensym)))\n    `(let ((,p ,path))\n       (with-open-file (,s ,p :direction :output :if-exists :supersede :if-does-not-exist :create)\n         (format ,s \"~A\" (random 1000000)))\n       (unwind-protect (progn ,@body)\n         (when (probe-file ,p) (delete-file ,p))))))",
